To run the test suite, change to this directory and run "./runtest". It runs
all test cases and lists unexpected outcomes. Adding the -v option shows
failure details. To run only particular applets:

./runtest <applet1> <applet2>...

Repository-local builds and tests must use Dockerfile.build. From the source
root, scripts/docker-testsuite.sh builds a defconfig BusyBox and runs this
suite in the build container.

Set SKIP_KNOWN_BUGS environment variable to any non-empty value
to exclude tests which are known to fail.

Set SKIP_INTERNET_TESTS to exclude tests which require working
internet connection.


Common causes of false positives:

For busybox built against uclibc, /etc/TZ does not exist or does not match
host system timezone setting. For glibc based host systems, timezone settings
are in /etc/localtime.

LANG and LC_xxx environment variables set to non-C locale.


Developer's notes:

All applet tests reside in files named command.tests and source testing.sh.
Use testing() when stdout and an exit status describe the assertion. Use
testing_script() with a here document for a multi-command test whose success
is determined by shell assertions. testing_script() runs every case in a new
temporary directory and removes it afterwards.

Use optional FEATURE_NAME before a test which needs a Kconfig feature and
reset SKIP afterwards. Tests that need the network should honor
SKIP_INTERNET_TESTS; known-bug cases should honor SKIP_KNOWN_BUGS.


